## Checklist

Before shipping a new graph, verify:

- [ ] Graph has at least one conditional edge (smart routing)
- [ ] There's a clear reason to use a graph vs. direct service calls
- [ ] State is defined in separate `.graph.state.ts` file
- [ ] Factory pattern with dependency injection
- [ ] All nodes have comprehensive logging (entry/exit)
- [ ] Error handling returns error state (doesn't throw)
- [ ] Conditional routing validates targets
- [ ] Fast paths exist for read-only operations (if applicable)
- [ ] Operation mode controls flow (create/read/update/delete)
- [ ] Tests cover conditional routing logic
